HEADWORD: old-maidish
<hw>old`-maid"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like an old
maid; prim; precise; particular; overly fastidious.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fussy, old-womanish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

